  "commentary": "With SPX at 7027.72 sitting just below the massive 7030 positive gamma wall (+11.98B), dealers are positioned to sell any push higher while providing buying support on dips given the PIN regime. The wall_break event suggests we just pierced through a key level, but the dense cluster of positive gamma walls from 7000-7050 creates a strong mean-reverting environment that should contain volatility. Watch 7030 as the critical inflection point - above it triggers dealer selling into 7050, while below brings dealer buying support with 7015 as the negative gamma pocket where buying accelerates.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 7000-7050 with limited breakout potential.",
